<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE GOODS; CHEAP THRILLS; EMMY-NOMINATED COSTUMES TAKE BOWS IN BEVERLY HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 See the costumes worn by the stars of "In Living Color," "Tales From the 
Crypt," "Dr. Quinn, Medicine Woman" and other television shows at Beverly 
Hill's annual display of Emmy-nominated costumes today through Sept. 4. The 
costumes, on display according to show, are all within walking distance of one 
another -- at stores such as I. Magnin, Saks Fifth Avenue and Tiffany & Co. 
Better yet, pick up the Beverly Hills trolley at the corner of Dayton Way and 
Rodeo Drive for a dollar, and take a tour of the city, which includes the 
costume display and a discussion of the designers (such as Bob Mackie, whose 
costumes for "Gypsy" are nominated). The trolley gives 20-minute tours of the 
city from 10 a.m.-5 p.m. daily. (800) 345-2210. Sample Beers From 
Micro-Breweries 
</P>
<P>
 Quench your thirst for exotic beers and eat out too, for less than it would 
cost to take a date to dinner. The Summer Karnival of Beers offers tastes of 
food and beer from 30 micro-breweries at Fullerton Hofbrau, 323 N. State 
College Blvd. The event benefits the Boys and Girls Club of Fullerton. Two-hour 
sittings begin at noon both days, ending Saturday at 11:30 p.m. and Sunday at 8 
p.m. $25; $12 for designated drivers (includes food, drinks). (714) 525-8241. 
Marvel Comics Mega Tour Is Coming to Town 
</P>
<P>
 Whether your heroes are on the level of Wolverine, Storm and Cyclops, or more 
the speed of Ren and Stimpy and Beavis and Butt-head, they will all be a part 
of the Marvel Comics Mega Tour, coming to the Los Angeles Airport Hilton, 10 
a.m.-6 p.m. Saturday. Admission is $5, children under 6 free -- but there are 
also tickets available at comics retailers for $2.50 (try Comics Unlimited in 
Hawaiian Gardens, Forbidden Planet in Sherman Oaks or Hi De Ho Comics in Santa 
Monica, to name a few). Marvel creator Stan Lee and several Marvel writers and 
artists will be there. (818) 995-0151. LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
