<HEADLINE>
<P>
TO REPENT IS HUMAN; IS TO ERR DIVINE? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re: The book review of "Galileo, A Life" ("A New Spin on Galileo, Science and 
the Catholic Church," Aug. 15): 
</P>
<P>
 In October, 1992, the Roman Catholic Church formally admitted 350 years after 
the fact (!) that it had erred in condemning Galileo Galilei . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Does this imply that, in the year 2344, the Church may finally admit error in 
its late 20th-Century views toward abortion, contraception and the 
out-of-control growth of world population? 
</P>
<P>
 Or would it be by then, perhaps, too late? 
</P>
<P>
 NIK GREEN, Goleta 
</P>
