<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMPASSIONATE DOCTOR TREATS FROM THE HEART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 While AIDS takes its toll on society, Dr. Scott Hitt refuses to stand by idle 
("Forever On Call," Aug. 14). He appears to be a man full of heart whose 
compassionate treatment of his patients is remembered by them. 
</P>
<P>
 On discrimination against gays, Hitt rightly points out: "There are lots of 
evil people out there who . . . believe that AIDS is retribution for an evil 
lifestyle and that being gay is against nature's laws. There is so much 
discrimination. . . ." 
</P>
<P>
 But it is reassuring and inspiring for me to know that Hitt continues his 
activities against AIDS, despite all the narrow-minded people out there. 
Wouldn't it be nice if there were more doctors like Hitt who take an active 
part in the community and who, in fact, truly care about people and not only 
money? 
</P>
<P>
 DAVID TULANIAN, West Hollywood 
