<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: UNITED WAY LOOKING FOR VOLUNTEERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 United Way of Ventura County is seeking volunteers to fan out across the 
county in a one-day campaign to clean trails, pack food and help elderly 
residents. 
</P>
<P>
 The campaign, called Day of Caring, is scheduled for Sept. 10.Volunteers will 
meet at 7:30 a.m. at either the Food Share headquarters in Oxnard or at 
California Lutheran University in Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 After a continental breakfast, volunteers will go to one of the project sites, 
where they will work from 9 to noon. Projects include cleaning trails in Ojai, 
picking up litter in county parks, doing errands for senior citizens and 
packing supplies for Food Share. 
</P>
<P>
 This is the sixth annual Day of Caring. About 600 people volunteered last 
year, and United Way officials said they expect the same or more this year. 
</P>
<P>
 To participate in the campaign, residents should call United Way at 485-6288. 
CHRISTINA LIMA 
