<P>
 The Senate Thursday night began a delayed summer recess until Sept. 12.The 
recess, which had been scheduled to start Aug. 12, came after final passage of 
President Clinton's crime bill. 
</P>
<P>
 Members of the House of Representatives, who unofficially began their recess 
last Sunday while awaiting Senate action, will be on vacation until Sept. 8. 
</P>
<P>
 The start of the congressional recess means that the President and First Lady 
Hillary Rodham Clinton can begin their summer vacation on Martha's Vineyard in 
