<P>
POLICE OFFICER IS SHOT, KILLED WITH HIS OWN GUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A police officer distributing parking permits for residents to use during a 
weekend religious festival was killed by a man who shot him three times in the 
chest with his own gun. 
</P>
<P>
 Raymond Cook, who lives in the building where Officer Thomas J. Giunta was 
shot, was charged with murder. Giunta, 44, and Cook, 46, argued before the 
shooting, police said. Neighbors said Cook had behaved oddly in the past. 
</P>
