<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: PORT HUENEME; MAN CHARGED IN FATAL STABBING AT 
MARKET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County prosecutors on Thursday charged a 32-year-old Port Hueneme man 
with fatally stabbing an employee at a convenience market during a botched 
robbery last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Adolfo Lopez Carrillo was arrested early Saturday on suspicion of killing 
Mohinder Bassi who worked at the B-Mart on East Pleasant Valley Road, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Bassi, 42, of Canoga Park was stabbed several times in the chest and stomach 
about 9:30 p.m. Aug. 19. He then staggered next door to a bar where patrons 
called an ambulance. After Carrillo's arrest, police said the stabbing happened 
during a failed robbery attempt. 
</P>
<P>
 Carrillo is scheduled to be arraigned Sept. 9 in Municipal Court. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to charging Carrillo with murder, prosecutors also filed 
allegations that he used a deadly weapon and inflicted great bodily injury. 
</P>
<P>
 Carrillo was being held in Ventura County Jail in lieu of $250,000 bail. JULIE 
FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
