<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; SUSPECT FLEES BAILIFFS BEFORE CASE IS 
CALLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Ventura man who had shown up in Ventura court to face about $17,000 in 
outstanding traffic- and narcotics-related warrants had a sudden change of 
heart Thursday -- and fled from stunned bailiffs, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Faced with the possibility of being remanded to deputies' custody, Rodney Page 
changed his mind about 3 p.m. in Division 10 of Ventura County Municipal Court 
and "split out the door with deputies giving chase," Sgt. Kenton Rainey said. 
</P>
<P>
 Page, 19, fled before Judge Roland N. Purnell even had a chance to call his 
case, the sergeant said. 
</P>
<P>
 Court bailiff Dan Russ joined the pursuit as it led authorities through a 
condominium complex at Telephone Road and County Square Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies and Ventura police, with the assistance of at least two canine units 
and a helicopter team, subsequently set up a perimeter that included an orange 
grove near Telephone Road and Victoria Avenue, but Page eluded them and 
remained at large. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities also were searching the neighborhood where some of Page's 
relatives live, Rainey said. GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
