<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA PAULA; APPLICANTS SOUGHT FOR PLANNING BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city of Santa Paula is soliciting applications to fill two seats on its 
seven-member Planning Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 City Administrator Arnold Dowdy said prospective commissioners must be 
registered voters who live in Santa Paula and be willing to attend two night 
meetings each month. 
</P>
<P>
 They also are required to file statements of economic interest with the 
California Fair Political Practices Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 The terms of incumbent commissioners Gabriella Reeves, appointed in 1991, and 
Shirley Hara, appointed in 1990, expire later this month, Dowdy said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Santa Paula Planning Commission is an advisory panel that makes 
recommendations on land-use and other applications to the Santa Paula City 
Council. 
</P>
<P>
 The deadline for applying is Wednesday. For more information, call city 
offices at 933-4200. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
