<P>
 Lloyd's Sued, Accused of Fraud: A Newport Beach man and his two daughters 
filed suit this week in Los Angeles County Superior Court, accusing Lloyd's of 
London of gulling them into investing in the world's oldest insurance market. 
The lawsuit claims Lloyd's concealed the risks involved, particularly the 
danger of large losses from asbestos and pollution liability cases. David F. 
West and his daughters, Deborah and Susan, also charge that Lloyd's violated 
California securities laws by failing to register with the state before it 
solicited their investments. 
