<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: COMPANY TOWN; FISCHER AND BUSBY FILL NEW POSTS AT MCA / 
UNIVERSAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MCA/Universal has promoted two executives to new senior-level positions. 
Joseph A. Fischer was named executive vice president of the MCA Motion Picture 
Group; Ann Busby will be senior vice president of the group.They and Jon 
Gumpert, legal and business affairs vice president, will assume the duties of 
former MCA executive Fred Bernstein. 
</P>
<P>
 * MGM/UA has named Rachel Aberly vice president of publicity for distribution 
and Marsha Gleeman president of the company's new music division. 
</P>
<P>
 * Geoffrey Darby has rejoined Viacom as president of Interactive Television 
Services. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ann Morfogen has been appointed vice president of communications at Sony 
Corp. of America. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nelvana Communications Inc. has promoted Bob Higgins to director of 
development. 
</P>
<P>
 Harry Garfield has been named senior vice president of music for Universal 
Pictures. 
</P>
<P>
 * Miramax Films has promoted Scott Greenstein to senior vice president of 
motion pictures, music, new media and publishing. 
</P>
<P>
 * Richard Ingber has joined Buena Vista Marketing, where he will oversee all 
aspects of marketing for Caravan Pictures. 
</P>
<P>
 * dick clark productions inc. has named Charles Candelas vice president of 
operations for the Dick Clark's American Bandstand Grill chain of restaurants. 
