<TEXT>
<P>
 K.V. Mart Co., owner of 13-store grocery chain accused in a lawsuit of labor 
violations, responded Thursday by denying the allegations and criticizing the 
Buena Park-based union that helped prepare the lawsuit. 
</P>
<P>
 Ty Hitt, chief financial officer of K.V. Mart in Long Beach, said his company 
pays "fair wages" to its 1,050 employees.A lawsuit filed Wednesday by six 
