<HEADLINE>
<P>
BARGAINS / GERI COOK: THE DECOR SCORE; FROM ARMOIRES TO UPHOLSTERED SOFAS, 
DESIGNERS FURNITURE MART OFFERS QUALITY AND REASONABLE PRICES. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GERI COOK, Geri Cook's Bargains column runs every Friday in Valley Life! 
Questions about shopping may be sent to her, in care of Valley Life!, Los 
Angeles Times, 20000 Prairie St., Chatsworth, CA 91311. Letters will not be 
answered individually, but topics of general interest will be discussed in 
future columns. Geri Cook can be heard from 9 to 10 a.m. Saturdays on KIEV 
870-AM. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Where L.A.'s Top Designers Shop" headlines one of the print ads for De 
signers Furniture Mart. I didn't run into any of Los Angeles' top designers 
while researching this store, but after checking out the inventory, I would say 
it's entirely possible that you might.  
</P>
<P>
 This is a family business, and owner John Green handpicks the styles. 
</P>
<P>
 The quality of the wood pieces, as well as the upholstered pieces, is quite 
good, considering that the prices are so reasonable. 
</P>
<P>
 The armoires are particularly well-priced: a pie/jelly cabinet -- excellent 
for storage or display -- in natural or waxed pine is only $247. Usually these 
run around $350. 
</P>
<P>
 An entertainment/storage center that is slightly bigger, in solid pine and 
with one adjustable shelf, is $295. As is the case with all of the wood pieces 
here, custom finishes are available. 
</P>
<P>
 A country bonnet-top armoire, with two adjustable shelves and a clothes rod, 
measures 78 inches high by 40 inches wide and is a reasonable $495 -- about 
$300 less than at many sources. Most wood pieces come from local manufacturers, 
and while we're not talking Century quality, they are made very well. 
</P>
<P>
 We reported recently on some slipcovered sofas at Mark Friedman's in Santa 
Monica, and here's another selection at a good price. 
</P>
<P>
 A 92-inch upholstered sofa -- and there's a wide range of fabrics to select 
from -- plus the slipcover of your choosing is $795. 
</P>
<P>
 All the sofas are kiln-dried elder wood, and the styles are transitional. The 
sofa-and-chair combo for $995 is a particularly good buy. 
</P>
<P>
 Several factors enhance the bargains on these sofa/slipcover combinations. 
</P>
<P>
 There is a lifetime warranty on the frames; a fabric protection treatment is 
offered at no cost; and you can trade in the slipcover at any time and receive 
a 50% credit applied to a new one. 
</P>
<P>
 Good-quality futons start at $167; check out the "clam bed" at $199. Sofa beds 
start at $395. 
</P>
<P>
 A handsome, queen-sized canopy bed was $399, and I've seen similar designs 
elsewhere for as high as $1,200. 
</P>
<P>
 Most of the prices are 30% to 40% below retail, some even lower. 
</P>
<P>
 There's a small "clearance" room upstairs that provides some super 
one-of-a-kind bargains. A four-drawer captain's bed of solid pine was priced at 
$249. WHERE TO SHOP 
</P>
<P>
 What: Designers Furniture Mart. 
</P>
<P>
 Location: 300 S. Brand Blvd., Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 Hours: 11 a.m. to 8 p.m. Monday through Friday, 10 a.m. to 7 p.m. Saturday, 
noon to 6 p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Cards: American Express, Discover, MasterCard, Visa. 
</P>
<P>
 Call: (818) 244-3061. 
</P>
