ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; MIDNIGHT OCEAN DIP FATAL TO SWIMMER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who went for a midnight ocean swim with a friend apparently drowned in 
the waves near Newport Pier, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, a man in his 20s believed to be from Riverside, did not come back 
up after a large wave toppled him and his friend about 12:30 a.m., police Sgt. 
Andy Gonis said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim's body turned up about four hours later. 
</P>
<P>
 The name of the man was not released, pending notification of relatives. 
Detectives investigating the case did not identify the friend. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonis said the incident did not appear to be the result of foul play. 
</P>
<P>
 The beach closes at 10 p.m. and no lifeguards were on duty at the time of the 
drowning, Gonis said. KEN ELLINGWOOD 
