ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; UC IRVINE TO OPEN EXTENSION BRANCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALICIA DI RADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine will open its first university extension branch in north Orange 
County next week, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 UCI Extension will offer 22 courses at the satellite location in Anaheim, UCI 
Extension spokeswoman Marguerite Bonous-Hammarth said.Classes begin Sept. 1. 
</P>
<P>
 The facility includes three classrooms where teachers will conduct daytime, 
evening and weekend classes, Bonous-Hammarth said. UCI Extension instructors 
will also organize customized classes for corporations and businesses at that 
site. 
</P>
<P>
 Classes offered during the first semester include Spanish for business 
professionals, basic Russian, handling hazardous materials emergencies and 
basic math and science review. 
</P>
<P>
 Classrooms will be based at 411 W. Broadway in Anaheim, Bonous-Hammarth said, 
until builders finish construction on a permanent two-story facility for UCI 
Extension in Anaheim in March, 1996. 
</P>
<P>
 For information on classes, call (714) 856-7942.ALICIA DI RADO 
</P>
