<P>
MAN WALKS INTO TRAFFIC, IS KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Anaheim man was killed Wednesday night after he walked into traffic on 
southbound Beach Boulevard and was struck by a woman driving a sports car, a 
spokesman with the Orange County Sheriff's Department said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ovidio Fajardo, 42, died at the scene about 10 p.m., sheriff's Lt. Dan Martini 
said. A team of investigators attended Fajardo's autopsy Thursday in an effort 
to reconstruct what happened. 
</P>
<P>
 "At this point, it appears to be the pedestrian's fault," Martini said. 
</P>
