<P>
BASEBALL STRIKE: DEVELOPMENTS FROM DAY 14 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Games lost: 12. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total games lost: 181. 
</P>
<P>
 * Games remaining: 488. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total income lost by players: $61.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Estimated revenue lost by owners: $119 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Key development: Talks broke off after a session that lasted about 90 
minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 * In quotes: "It's just my opinion, but I don't think there is going to be any 
more baseball played this year."  
</P>
<P>
 -- Curt Schilling 
</P>
<P>
