<TEXT>
<P>
 O.C. AIR: Quarterbacks from Orange County will make their presence felt in the 
Pacific 10 Conference this year. Three starters and two key reserves played 
high school football here. A series beginning Sunday in The Times assesses the 
area as a breeding ground for top quarterbacks and looks at the three starters 
-- Steve Stenstrom (Stanford, El Toro), Rob Johnson (USC, El Toro) and Danny 
O'Neil (Oregon, Mater Dei) -- and the potential stars of tomorrow -- Tim Carey 
(Stanford, Los Alamitos) and Pat Barnes (Cal, Trabuco Hills). 
</P>
