<HEADLINE>
<P>
PHONE CHATTER COMES BACK AS A WINNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Phone Chatter, last year's 2-year-old filly champion, made her first start in 
10 months Thursday and rallied from last to win the $55,600 C.E.R.F. Stakes by 
a length over Airistar at Del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
 Ridden by Laffit Pincay and carrying 117 pounds, Phone Chatter covered 6 1/2 
furlongs in 1:15. She paid $3, $2.60, $2.20. 
</P>
<P>
 Airistar returned $4 and $3, while Klassy Kim, another half-length back in 
third, was $3.20 to show. 
</P>
<P>
 Phone Chatter hadn't competed since fracturing her hind leg while winning the 
Breeders' Cup Juvenile Fillies on Nov. 6. She won the Eclipse Award as the 
nation's top 2-year-old filly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
