<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: CANOGA PARK; PROSTITUTE SENTENCED FOR VIOLATING BAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Canoga Park woman was sentenced to 90 days in jail for violating a ban on 
convicted prostitutes engaging in conversation or soliciting motorists during 
nighttime hours in areas of the San Fernando Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Peaches Wilson, 40, was taken into custody about 10:15 Sunday in Canoga Park 
after she approached and solicited an undercover police officer, according to 
City Atty.James Hahn's office. 
</P>
<P>
 Prostitutes on probation are prohibited from talking to motorists, asking for 
or accepting rides and being in parked cars with motorists between 5 p.m. and 6 
a.m. on certain segments of Sepulveda, Lankershim, Ventura and Reseda 
boulevards as well as Sherman Way, according to the city attorney's office. 
</P>
<P>
 On Aug. 4, Wilson pleaded no contest to soliciting and was placed on three 
years probation. MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
