<P>
PACOIMA MAN HELD IN DEATH OF ROOMMATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police on Thursday arrested a 47-year-old Pacoima man who they say killed his 
62-year-old roommate with a blunt object and dumped the man's body along the 
side of Whitnall Highway in North Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 Bennie Lee Carmack was arrested at the mobile home he shared with Roy Haselow 
on Glenoaks Boulevard, said Lt. Joseph Garcia of the Los Angeles Police 
Department. The two men argued before the killing and police are continuing to 
investigate the motive, Garcia said. 
</P>
<P>
 A passerby discovered Haselow's body on Wednesday in bushes along the highway 
near Cahuenga Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 Carmack is expected to be arraigned today, Garcia said. 
</P>
