<HEADLINE>
<P>
OC HIGH: STUDENT NEWS AND VIEWS; LITERARY TEENS HAVE THEIR SAY IN WRITES OF 
PASSAGE MAGAZINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ASSOCIATED PRESS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Writes of Passage is a new national teen-age literary magazine developed to 
give junior high and high school students a national forum in which to express 
themselves through creative writing. 
</P>
<P>
 The premiere issue for spring-summer 1994 ($5.95) consists of poems and short 
stories from 40 teen-agers representing 15 states.Also included are brief 
biographies of each student published, an interview with a well-known young 
adult novelist and an ongoing story created by combining different submissions, 
called To be continued . . .  
</P>
<P>
 Writes of Passage Inc. is an educational, nonprofit organization dedicated to 
promoting creative expression through teen-age reading and writing. The 
founders and editors of the magazine are Laura Hoffman and Wendy Mass, who were 
roommates at Tufts University. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Writes of Passage is available by subscription. A one-year-subscription is 
$12. Two issues are scheduled for fall-winter 1994-95 and spring-summer 1995. 
Thereafter, the magazine is to be published quarterly. For subscriptions or 
more information, contact Writes of Passage Inc., Box 7676, Greenwich, CN 
06836.  
</P>
