<P>
'SILENTS ON SUNDAYS' TO FEATURE WOMEN IN HOLLYWOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Silents on Sundays: Women in Hollywood" will be presented at 1 p.m. on the 
first three Sundays in September in the Pio Pico Gallery of the Homestead 
Museum, 15415 East Don Julian Road, City of Industry. 
</P>
<P>
 The series, screened on video, starts with a program of short comedies, "Her 
Bridal Nightmare" (1920), with Colleen Moore; "Campus Carmen" (1928), with 
Carole Lombard; and "A Luck Would Have It" (1918), with Betty Compson. 
</P>
<P>
 Sept. 11: "The Extra Girl" (1923), starring Mabel Normand. 
</P>
<P>
 Sept. 18: "It" (1928), with Clara Bow. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (818) 968-8492. 
