<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: CLEVELAND HIGH ADDS MILLS TO BASEBALL STAFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE ELLING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cleveland High has named Jim Mills co-coach of the baseball team. 
</P>
<P>
 Mills, who last season was an assistant at Chaminade, will work with Steve 
Landress, the team's coach the past three seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 Mills, a walk-on coach who is self-employed, isn't exactly an unknown quantity 
at Cleveland. He is a football assistant for the Cavaliers and an alumnus of 
the school. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's knowledgeable in the sport and he's a good disciplinarian," said Everett 
Macy, Cleveland's athletic director. "He'll really be good for the program, a 
definite asset." 
</P>
<P>
 Cleveland finished 3-20 last spring and was last in the North Valley League at 
2-15. The Cavaliers were 6-14-1, 5-12 in 1993. STEVE ELLING 
</P>
